category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com

category.name: support
description:
Bonjour et Bienvenue dans votre groupe « Coaching de vie privée et professionnelle et surtout de la bonne humeur ».
L’accomplissement personnel est l’une des clés du bonheur. Ce groupe ouvre ses portes aujourd’hui le 26 janvier 2017. Je suis sur que nous serons très vite nombreux dans notre belle région à être sensible à ces divers sujets qui tournent autour du sens de l'humain.
Même si l’éducation national le relègue encore à de la futilité. Et pourtant, nous sommes bien les heureux propriétaires de la machine la plus performante que l’homme n’ai jamais crée. Et pourtant personne ne nous a vraiment expliqué son fonctionnement. 
« Petit j’aurai aimé qu’une personne m’explique, ce que sont les émotions ? Comment ça marche ? Quel est leur rôle ? 

- Ou bien, pourquoi est-ce que j’ai des ressentiments, quel est leur sens ?
- Ou bien c’est quoi cette petite voix interne qui me critique ? Qui me dit « tu peux le faire ou pas, tu n’y arriveras pas, ce job n'est pas fait pour toi, ou c'est trop beau pour toi...etc ».

Comme tout le monde la vie nous confronte à des problématiques. Comment devenir acteurs de ces situations pour ne plus les subir et les dépasser. Pourquoi reproduit-on des comportements, des attitudes. D'ou nous viennent certaines croyances nous concernant, pouvons nous les modifier et s'en affranchir ? 

Ce groupe accueille des personnes de tous horizons, de tous âges, de toutes professions. Le lien entre chacun de ses membres (au-delà du lien universel :) réside dans l’intérêt commun porté à l’évolution personnelle consciente.
Des rencontres et des partages sur différents sujets autour de l’humain et de son accomplissement. Quelle est notre raison d’être, si ce n’est que celle de nous réaliser ici est maintenant et pleinement ? 

Nous avons tous les mêmes aspirations : aimer et être aimé, être heureux et nous réaliser.
Je vous laisse découvrir tout cela par vous-même puisque rien ne vaut l’expérience directe et concrète des choses…
Voici les différents ateliers que je vous propose tout au long de l’année, à raison d’un à deux fois par mois. Soit le lundi matin ou le mercredi matin à 9h autour d’un petit déjeuner (Une boisson plus une pâtisserie).
Duré : 1h30
Lieux : CRESCENDO : Galeries Lafayette, 25 Avenue du Parmelan, 74000 Annecy

Ateliers échanges débats :
- Les émotions : Quel est leurs rôles ? Ennemies ou amies ?
- Le OUI : Quel est le sens de notre oui ? Quand je dis oui à l’autre est-ce que c’est aussi un oui pour moi ?
- L’image de soi : Qu’est-ce que c’est ? comment impact elle notre vie ?
- Que voulez-vous dans votre vie ? le petit feu ou bien la grande cheminée ?
- Et si je décidais de me traiter en 1ère classe. L’égoïsme sain ça vous parle ?
- Le célibat : Un choix ou subi ?
- L’autre : Qui est-il ? Est-il moi ?
- Etre ou avoir ? ou les deux ?
- Les croyances : Et si ce que je croyais était faux ? comment seraient les choses ?
- Estime de soi : Comment est-ce que je me parle ? Quel importance a mon dialogue interne sur mon attitude ?
- L’amour de soi : Est-ce que je m’aime vraiment ? Aujourd’hui je décide de m’aimer avec tous mes défauts et mes manques.
- Je suis un être en perpétuel transformation.
- La chance : C’est quoi la chance pour vous ? 

 Merci de noter que pour des raisons de logistique, nous limitons les inscriptions des ateliers  à 15 personnes. Merci beaucoup pour votre compréhension…
D’autre part, ces groupes sont annoncés sur d’autres plateformes que Meetup afin de ne pas privilégier un public en particulier. 


Je suis Hacen JEAIDI (Coach Personnel & Professionnel et Formateur sur la région Annecienne). Certifié par l'institut de coaching International de Genève. Certifié en PNL par BANDLER. 

Vous trouverez ma mini-biographie dans mon profil. Vous pouvez également me retrouver sur Facebook et LinkedIn. 

https://www.facebook.com/Hacenjeaidicoach/?ref=bookmarks

http://www.jeaidihacen.com/accueil/particuliers-2/mon-aimant-interieur/

A votre réussite et bien plus encore

http://www.jeaidihacen.com/

Hacen,

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

This is a group done for people who are willing to go out of their comfort zone by doing funny challenges. An excellent way to face your fears and to be more confident. Afterwards we'll do some improvised talks!!
Then, we'll head out into the city and we'll do some challenges!

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

description:
Hi5!
This is a group done for people who are willing to go out of their comfort zone by doing funny challenges. An excellent way to face your fears and to be more confident. After a short introduction, we'll set our weekly goals in the accountability exercise. If you ever wanted to change your habits, this is the exercise for you!
Afterwards we'll do some improvised talks!!
Then, we'll head out into the city and we'll do some challenges!

Join our Private Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/1904642849854177/

Feel free to bring some snacks with you.

description:
Hey there! This is a social and support group for people who are suffering (or recovering) from anxiety, depression, OCD, social anxiety or other related issues.

It's basically a safe and comfortable environment to meet other people who might be facing similar issues - and to feel a little less alone in this world!

We'll have events like movie nights, cafe's, lunch/dinner, picnics, hiking trips, etc. Events will typically be fairly small (usually 4-8 people) so that everyone is comfortable.

description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)

category.name: support
description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)
name: Konstanz Alcoholics Anonymous Meetup

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com
name: Gateway Women Europe: United not Defined by Childlessness

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen
organizer.name: Maria Wiasmitinowa

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

description:
Hi5!
This is a group done for people who are willing to go out of their comfort zone by doing funny challenges. An excellent way to face your fears and to be more confident. After a short introduction, we'll set our weekly goals in the accountability exercise. If you ever wanted to change your habits, this is the exercise for you!
Afterwards we'll do some improvised talks!!
Then, we'll head out into the city and we'll do some challenges!

Join our Private Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/1904642849854177/

Feel free to bring some snacks with you.

description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

description:
Hi5!
This is a group done for people who are willing to go out of their comfort zone by doing funny challenges. An excellent way to face your fears and to be more confident. After a short introduction, we'll set our weekly goals in the accountability exercise. If you ever wanted to change your habits, this is the exercise for you!
Afterwards we'll do some improvised talks!!
Then, we'll head out into the city and we'll do some challenges!

Join our Private Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/1904642849854177/

Feel free to bring some snacks with you.

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

description: Dies ist eine Gruppe für Personen, die unter einer schweren Trennung oder Scheidung leiden. category.name: support
description:
Hey there! This is a social and support group for people who are suffering (or recovering) from anxiety, depression, OCD, social anxiety or other related issues.

It's basically a safe and comfortable environment to meet other people who might be facing similar issues - and to feel a little less alone in this world!

We'll have events like movie nights, cafe's, lunch/dinner, picnics, hiking trips, etc. Events will typically be fairly small (usually 4-8 people) so that everyone is comfortable.

category.name: support
description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)
name: Konstanz Alcoholics Anonymous Meetup

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen

Für Englisch und Deutsch Sprechern.)

category.name: support
description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)
name: Konstanz Alcoholics Anonymous Meetup

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen

Für Englisch und Deutsch Sprechern.)

category.name: support
description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)
name: Konstanz Alcoholics Anonymous Meetup

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

category.name: support
description:
Hi5!
This is a group done for people who are willing to go out of their comfort zone by doing funny challenges. An excellent way to face your fears and to be more confident. After a short introduction, we'll set our weekly goals in the accountability exercise. If you ever wanted to change your habits, this is the exercise for you!
Afterwards we'll do some improvised talks!!
Then, we'll head out into the city and we'll do some challenges!

Join our Private Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/1904642849854177/

Feel free to bring some snacks with you.

category.name: support
description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen
organizer.name: Maria Wiasmitinowa

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen

category.name: support
description:
THIS IS A CLOSED GROUP - NONE OF THE INFORMATION YOU WRITE ON OUR PAGES IS EITHER SEARCHABLE BY GOOGLE OR VISIBLE TO NON-GROUP MEMBERS. WE UNDERSTAND THAT BEING CHILDLESS CAN BE TOUGH TO BE OPEN ABOUT AND WE RESPECT AND PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

[img src="http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/even..." unselectable="on">

This Meetup Group is for European-based childless-by-circumstance women. Those circumstances might include infertility, not meeting the right partner in time (or yet), your partner not wanting (more children) and so many other ways that we can end up not being mothers when that wasn't the plan!

One of the things about not having children when most of your peers do can be that your social circle dwindles or dries up completely. This can leave you feeling very left out of 'normal' life - which in turn can make dealing with the unexpected situation you find yourself in even tricker on some days! 

Once your membership has been approved, please adjust your meetup settings so that you only recieve notifcations for meetups within a variable radius of your address, so that you don't get bombarded for meetups in Paris when you live in Madrid or Geneve!

http://youtu.be/tvXScNU6GAM

Here at Gateway Women our motto is: 

We may not be mothers but we're here, we care, we count and we ROCK!!

If you're childfree (ie: childless-by-choice) you're welcome to join us, but you'll find that most of us are childless-by-circumstance which means that we wanted to have children (or are still hoping to one day) but:

• we didn't (or haven't yet) met the right partner

• we've got infertility issues

• we've come to the end of fertility treatments

• becoming a voluntary single-mother isn't right for us

• we've got partners who don't want children (or more children)

• we've got genetic or medical conditions that mean we've chosen not to have children

• we're ineligible as adoptive parents

• adoption isn't right for us

However, I know that 'childfree' isn't an easy choice and creates many of the same identity and social issues as being childless not by choice. The grief may be different, but as long as you are sensitive to the difference, you will be totally welcome. 

There are so many reasons why a woman doesn't have children, and this is one group where no-one will mouth well-meaning platitudes at you! Or even talk about it because it's the ONLY place that you won't have to explain how complicated and loaded childlessness can be in our culture right now!

Gateway Women also hosts a private online community over on G+ which you're very welcome to join also. Often members get to know each other there and then progress to meeting each other face-to-face via this Meetup group. That's where most of our international members are.

Gateway Women can be any age with the majority of us are from our late-30s to late-50s. Some of us have partners, some of us are single, some of us are divorced, some of us don't fit any of those categories and that's fine too. Heterosexual, bi and gay members welcome.

Gateway Women are a band of very diverse women, but we all share the feeling of 'not fitting in' to a culture that doesn't seem to have a place for us.

You're not weird. You're not alone. You're a Gateway Woman.

And this is your Tribe. Welcome!

Jody Day 
Founder of Gateway Women & Author of "Rocking the Life Unexpected: 12 Weeks to Your Plan B for a Meaningful and Fulfiling Life Without Children" 
www.gateway-women.com

category.name: support
description:
At the base of our life lies a deep desire to contribute to our own happiness and the happiness of others.
The main obstacle to this desire is the language that we have learned- a language that leads to disconnection and separation.

Learning to communicate with ourselves and with others compassionately through what M. Rosenberg – founder of Nonviolent Communication - calls “language of life” enables us - to recognise and acknowledge our emotions and feelings
- to identify and embrace what motivates our choices and the choices of others (our partner, our children, our parents, our friends, our colleagues and even those who seem very far away)
- to identify and transform our thoughts and our judgments
- to listen to ourselves and others with empathy

Such language has the power to revolutionize our intimate and our professional relationships

We will learn and experience the key elements of Nonviolent Communication.
Nonviolent Communication is first and foremost a practice. Therefore the experience will be the foundation of the seminar.
After a weekend, you will have the tools to start using this "new language" in your daily life, and transforming conflicts into opportunities for emphatic connection.
name: Communicate with Empathy- Move beyond fear, shame and guilt

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. 

We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)
name: Konstanz Alcoholics Anonymous Meetup

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
Hey there! This is a social and support group for people who are suffering (or recovering) from anxiety, depression, OCD, social anxiety or other related issues.

It's basically a safe and comfortable environment to meet other people who might be facing similar issues - and to feel a little less alone in this world!

We'll have events like movie nights, cafe's, lunch/dinner, picnics, hiking trips, etc. Events will typically be fairly small (usually 4-8 people) so that everyone is comfortable.

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
name: Winterthur Angststörungen
organizer.name: Maria Wiasmitinowa

category.name: support
description:
Hey there! This is a social and support group for people who are suffering (or recovering) from anxiety, depression, OCD, social anxiety or other related issues.

It's basically a safe and comfortable environment to meet other people who might be facing similar issues - and to feel a little less alone in this world!

We'll have events like movie nights, cafe's, lunch/dinner, picnics, hiking trips, etc. Events will typically be fairly small (usually 4-8 people) so that everyone is comfortable.

description: This is a group for people actively engaged in overcoming multiple sclerosis, for the sharing of research, ideas, feelings, tips, traps, and stories. description: Dies ist eine Gruppe für Personen, die unter einer schweren Trennung oder Scheidung leiden. We meet every Thursday from 19:30 to 20:30 at Cherisy-Straße 13, 78467 Konstanz

*Note, GPS: 47.679703, 9.161143 (some of the online maps point to the wrong place)

1st Meeting of the month: Step - Study (12& 12) (or Speaker Meeting)

2nd Meeting of the month: Tradition - Study (12&12) (or Speaker Meeting)

3rd Meeting of the month: Reading Living Sober (or Speaker Meeting) 

4th (& 5th) Meeting of the month: Big Book – Study (or Speaker Meeting)

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria

category.name: support
description:
Du hast Panikattacken? Du verlässt kaum das Haus aus Angst? Bei jedem körperlichen Symptom bist du überzeugt an einer schweren Krankheit zu leiden? Du machst dir ständig Sorgen? Du glaubst, dass bald etwas ganz schlimmes passiert? Du kannst dein Leben einfach nicht mehr so geniessen wie früher? Menschen mit einer Angststörung haben es sehr schwer. Äusserlich sehen sie gesund aus. Innerlich sind sie halb tot. Sie fühlen sich allein gelassen. Können es kaum glauben, dass es anderen Menschen auch so ergeht. Es gibt viele Fragen.

Trete dieser Gruppe bei, wenn du selbst daran leidest oder gelitten hast und nun deine Erfahrungen mit Leidenden teilen möchtest. Wir treffen uns, lernen uns kennen und stärken uns gegenseitig.

Hier hast du einen Ort, an dem du dich verstanden fühlst, Fragen stellen kannst, Ideen und Tipps bekommst oder neue Hoffnung schöpfst um aus dem Teufelskreis zu entkommen.

Liebe Grüsse
Maria
